        "6": {
            "notes": "We learned \"That's not a real word.\"\n\nWe started learning Iris in ASL from this video https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R-xxD_VkiC4 its really fun. We got up to 0:43. I already forgot everything after the first verse except for Heaven but it was fun! Also im confused about the some sign, she does it differently than thee ppl on the websites.\n\nWe also role played this conversation minus the name spelling:\n\nAnna: Hello! How are you?\n\n    ASL: HELLO. HOW YOU?\n\nSarah: Hi! I am good, thank you. How are you?\n\n    ASL: HI. I GOOD, THANK-YOU. HOW YOU?\n\nAnna: I am fine. My name is Anna. What is your name?\n\n    ASL: I FINE. MY NAME A-N-N-A (fingerspelled). YOUR NAME WHAT?\n\nSarah: Nice to meet you. My name is Sarah.\n\n    ASL: NICE MEET YOU. MY NAME S-A-R-A-H (fingerspelled).\n\nAnna: Nice to meet you too.\n ",
            "signs": [
                "Stop",
                "Word",
                "Real",
                "That's",
                "Shut up",
                "game",
                "Playing",
                "Forever",
                "Give up",
                "Heaven"
            ],
            "tools": [
